WEBVTT

00:19.825 --> 00:43.329
[SPEAKER_01]: Hello and welcome to Veterans of the Valley.

00:43.650 --> 00:44.871
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm Tom Turbyville.

00:45.678 --> 00:52.428
[SPEAKER_01]: December the 19th, 1941, Ed Eyre was among the first to volunteer for service following the attack on Pearl Harbor.

00:52.929 --> 00:57.195
[SPEAKER_01]: It took a while, a little maneuvering to get where he wanted to be as a Marine.

00:57.215 --> 01:02.303
[SPEAKER_01]: He wanted to fight for his country in the Pacific and eventually he found himself in the middle of it.

01:02.671 --> 01:11.300
[SPEAKER_01]: a member of the 5th Marine Division, 28th Regimental Weapons Company, charging the sands on D-Day at Iwo Jima, February the 19th, 1945.

01:12.242 --> 01:13.203
[SPEAKER_01]: He saw that U.S.

01:13.223 --> 01:21.552
[SPEAKER_01]: flag flying atop Mount Suribachi, the flag etched in American pride by the famous photograph of the Marines who mounted it there.

01:21.572 --> 01:27.879
[SPEAKER_01]: He fought day and night at Iwo Jima for 10 days until shrapnel from a mortar round eventually ended his combat service.

01:28.559 --> 01:31.783
[SPEAKER_01]: Ed Eyre, winner of the Bronze Star and the Purple Heart,

01:32.084 --> 01:35.831
[SPEAKER_01]: lives in rural Brassens County, and what an honor it is to be visiting with you.

01:36.112 --> 01:37.715
[SPEAKER_01]: We had a chance to visit the other day.

01:38.016 --> 01:47.314
[SPEAKER_01]: You really wanted to get into where the action was, and that's why you joined up just a few days after Pearl Harbor, but you had a little trouble getting to where the action was.

01:47.334 --> 01:51.021
[SPEAKER_01]: You had to sort of jump through some hoops as it were to talk about that.

01:52.942 --> 01:59.471
[SPEAKER_00]: Okay, in December of 41, the Marine Corps had only two divisions, the first division, second division.

02:00.272 --> 02:12.929
[SPEAKER_00]: And after I finished boot camp, I went to a nearby camp there at Camp Elliott, north of San Diego, to form the third division, which made some sense.

02:12.949 --> 02:17.515
[SPEAKER_00]: So we trained there until July, and at that point,

02:17.495 --> 02:32.583
[SPEAKER_00]: decided that they needed a 4th Division, so they took half of us, sent us to the East Coast, and I got the chance now to do the same thing in the 4th Division, which was acting as a rifleman, BAR man, motorman, whatever the duty was I might have had at that time.

02:33.244 --> 02:38.895
[SPEAKER_00]: And at that point, my friend and I decided that we wanted to get into action the best we

02:39.213 --> 02:44.950
[SPEAKER_00]: The way we thought we could was to go and volunteer for the parachute regiment, which we did.

02:44.970 --> 02:52.092
[SPEAKER_00]: We went to our training in North Carolina, got our wings, and was sent right to New Caledonia.

02:53.270 --> 02:54.391
[SPEAKER_00]: For more training.

02:54.411 --> 02:55.452
[SPEAKER_01]: For more training.

02:55.472 --> 02:55.833
[SPEAKER_00]: For more training.

02:55.853 --> 02:56.374
[SPEAKER_01]: For more training.

02:56.394 --> 03:01.239
[SPEAKER_01]: And it was about this time that it was really frustrating because I think you said the third and the fourth sort of went by you.

03:01.279 --> 03:03.582
[SPEAKER_01]: They were over at the Pacific and you were still training, right?

03:03.602 --> 03:07.026
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes, they got into action before we did.

03:07.046 --> 03:14.454
[SPEAKER_00]: And we finally left New Caledonia, went up to, in the Solomons, to Vela Lavella, which is a small island there.

03:15.395 --> 03:20.761
[SPEAKER_00]: And then from that point, we were used as just infantry on Bougainville.

03:20.781 --> 03:22.483
[SPEAKER_00]: We never did make a combat jump.

03:22.919 --> 03:26.484
[SPEAKER_00]: at all because of the terrain in the South Pacific.

03:26.924 --> 03:29.668
[SPEAKER_00]: So we went on to Bougainville.

03:30.328 --> 03:39.460
[SPEAKER_01]: Talk more about your service there in Bougainville because this was really your first tour of the Pacific and this was the first time that you actually saw combat action, although it was on the ground.

03:39.480 --> 03:43.385
[SPEAKER_01]: This was the Northern Solomon Islands part of the Pacific Campaign.

03:43.465 --> 03:45.788
[SPEAKER_01]: Talk about what your job was there.

03:46.105 --> 04:05.266
[SPEAKER_00]: Well, as we landed, we were about four days behind the initial landing, the 1st Marine Parachute Regiment, and we received the assignment to go up through the lines and to secure a hill called 1,000, being 1,000 feet above sea level.

04:05.906 --> 04:09.430
[SPEAKER_00]: And our job was to take that because it was the commanding ground

04:09.410 --> 04:19.803
[SPEAKER_00]: could oversee the entire Torquina River Basin, which is the place on Bougainville that they wanted to put a fighter strip and a bomber strip.

04:19.823 --> 04:23.147
[SPEAKER_00]: So our job was to get up there on the hill and hold it.

04:23.748 --> 04:30.096
[SPEAKER_00]: And we saw some action up there with the Japanese, or the enemy, I'll call them, trying to take it back.

04:30.817 --> 04:34.001
[SPEAKER_00]: And we were there on the hill about seven days.

04:34.362 --> 04:38.607
[SPEAKER_00]: And then we're relieved, taken back and sent back to Guadalcanal

04:39.380 --> 04:43.602
[SPEAKER_01]: This was around 1943, I believe you said that it was, and eventually,

04:44.172 --> 04:51.243
[SPEAKER_01]: the Marines disbanded all of these troops and you went back home for a while, I guess, to wait for your next assignment.

04:51.263 --> 04:51.683
[SPEAKER_00]: Correct.

04:52.184 --> 05:02.239
[SPEAKER_00]: The Marine Corps at that time disbanded the parachute regiment, the raiders, and several other special units that we had.

05:02.259 --> 05:08.008
[SPEAKER_00]: We were all sent back to the United States and given furlough.

05:08.028 --> 05:13.656
[SPEAKER_00]: Went back to Camp Pendleton and got to organize the 5th Marine Division.

05:13.636 --> 05:18.564
[SPEAKER_01]: You said one time that if you ever had a reunion, you'd be pretty busy because you remember just about all of them.

05:18.584 --> 05:20.727
[SPEAKER_00]: I can go to all three of them.

05:20.747 --> 05:25.354
[SPEAKER_01]: But the 5th Division, this is where you pretty much earned your stripes, as it were, was in the 5th Division.

05:25.394 --> 05:26.836
[SPEAKER_01]: Training Camp Pendleton, is that right?

05:26.996 --> 05:28.118
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes.

05:28.138 --> 05:32.925
[SPEAKER_01]: And you were in the Regimental Weapons Company.

