06:01.399 --> 06:05.288
[SPEAKER_00]: The half tracks mounted a 75 millimeter cannon.

06:05.949 --> 06:16.110
[SPEAKER_00]: And that's the purpose of the Regimental Weapons Company is to be a support group as needed, move to different units as they needed to support.

06:16.192 --> 06:16.472
[SPEAKER_01]: Right.

06:16.953 --> 06:20.137
[SPEAKER_01]: You were initially a rifleman though, right?

06:20.257 --> 06:22.139
[SPEAKER_00]: Oh, every Marine is a rifleman.

06:22.159 --> 06:22.760
[SPEAKER_00]: That's the first.

06:23.461 --> 06:28.346
[SPEAKER_00]: You go through boot camp and you come out of there a rifleman, trained to be a rifleman.

06:28.386 --> 06:35.495
[SPEAKER_00]: So even if you go to Cook's and Baker School or get into intelligence or supply, you're still basically a rifleman.

06:35.515 --> 06:37.857
[SPEAKER_00]: You can take that rifle and you know what to do with it.

06:37.958 --> 06:38.318
[SPEAKER_01]: Indeed.

06:38.518 --> 06:41.001
[SPEAKER_01]: But you eventually moved to 60 Mortars.

06:41.021 --> 06:41.281
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes.

06:41.902 --> 06:43.264
[SPEAKER_01]: But your first, I want to go back to the rifle.

06:43.284 --> 06:46.047
[SPEAKER_01]: You said your first rifle was pretty much a relic, wasn't it?

06:46.027 --> 07:12.760
[SPEAKER_01]: well it's what we had it was a 1903 springfield the 30-06 a bolt action nice weapon did a good job it predated the m1 though yes absolutely yeah that was uh the 28th marine uh uh regimental uh weapons company that's what you were a member of now let's uh your next assignment you moved back to the pacific and you made your way eventually to iwo jima talk about

07:13.043 --> 07:20.649
[SPEAKER_01]: sort of the trip there and getting there and the preparation, your mind preparation and physical preparation to go to battle at Iwo Jima.

