07:35.036 --> 07:36.899
[SPEAKER_00]: We did our training separately.

07:37.579 --> 07:52.737
[SPEAKER_00]: And then we would advance to the problems, as they call them, as a company or battalion would go out and set up a situation where they would call on us and it would be up to us to see how we could support them.

07:53.375 --> 07:58.061
[SPEAKER_01]: Iwo Jima, it's obviously an island that has a lot of fame.

07:58.081 --> 08:01.045
[SPEAKER_01]: There have been Hollywood movies made about it.

08:01.065 --> 08:03.689
[SPEAKER_01]: Talk a little bit about what the importance was of this island.

08:03.749 --> 08:16.125
[SPEAKER_01]: I know that its geography was one of the main reasons that it was so important to the American effort in the Pacific, just where it was located between Japan and the bomber bases, right?

08:16.527 --> 08:17.188
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes, correct.

08:17.248 --> 08:24.798
[SPEAKER_00]: The Iwo is about 750 miles, rough figure, from Japan.

08:25.499 --> 08:33.450
[SPEAKER_00]: And our bombers were leaving the Marianas, Saipan, and it was quite a long trip for them.

08:33.951 --> 08:44.205
[SPEAKER_00]: And they would bomb Japan, and of course they were subject to mechanical problems, they were subject to enemy fighters, anti-aircraft fire, and just running short of fuel.

08:44.557 --> 08:50.124
