09:23.052 --> 09:25.596
[SPEAKER_01]: Right, and there were plenty of those, as we'll mention in a minute.

09:26.498 --> 09:37.497
[SPEAKER_01]: So essentially, it was a sanctuary for bombers that were crippled, that needed refueling, because the bombers simply did not have the range that it took to get from the Marianas to

09:37.477 --> 09:38.719
[SPEAKER_01]: to the Japanese island.

09:38.739 --> 09:42.264
[SPEAKER_00]: Well, essentially they did under in a perfect world.

09:42.605 --> 09:49.816
[SPEAKER_00]: But if you got a headwind or something that's gonna change the fuel consumption, then he's gonna run short of fuel.

09:49.976 --> 09:52.440
[SPEAKER_01]: So this is why Iwo Jima was so important.

09:52.480 --> 09:57.207
[SPEAKER_01]: But the Japanese had many, many years to prepare that particular island.

09:57.187 --> 10:00.391
[SPEAKER_01]: for whatever it took to defend it.

10:00.571 --> 10:04.455
[SPEAKER_01]: So it was, they were pretty intent on keeping it also.

10:04.575 --> 10:05.116
[SPEAKER_00]: Absolutely.

10:05.436 --> 10:12.324
[SPEAKER_00]: And yes, they had, in my recollection, about 20 years that they had their forces stationed there.

10:12.344 --> 10:20.654
[SPEAKER_00]: So they had a good chance to dig in, create caves, do all the things necessary to make a good defensive position.

10:20.734 --> 10:24.578
[SPEAKER_01]: We're gonna see a photograph of one of those caves in a little bit.

10:24.794 --> 10:27.378
[SPEAKER_01]: Let's talk about D-Day, February the 19th, 1945.

10:28.139 --> 10:33.107
[SPEAKER_01]: What do you remember about that day and how it developed as you all hit the beach?

10:36.012 --> 10:43.123
[SPEAKER_00]: Well, it wasn't much to look at as you looked over the front of the LCVP, the landing craft that we were in because it was just a very,

10:43.357 --> 10:51.628
[SPEAKER_00]: flat island, didn't rise up out of the water more than, seemed like about 10 or 12 feet, no trees whatsoever, big mountain.

10:52.289 --> 11:03.103
[SPEAKER_00]: It turned out to be a volcano on the left, and so we just wondered why we had to have this piece of real estate, but it turned out we did, and we did.

11:03.083 --> 11:10.335
[SPEAKER_01]: A lot of the bombing that had happened before you all ever got there had really pretty much destroyed any vegetation there was there.

11:10.675 --> 11:13.620
[SPEAKER_01]: So once you got there, there was really nowhere to hide.

11:14.602 --> 11:19.950
[SPEAKER_01]: Your only recourse was pretty much frontal assault, and there weren't many trees and things like that to hide behind.

11:19.970 --> 11:22.895
[SPEAKER_00]: Not a one, not a one on the south end of the island.

11:23.576 --> 11:30.407
[SPEAKER_00]: Toward the north end, they had more gullies and a little better cover, but certainly not adequate.

11:30.640 --> 11:35.207
[SPEAKER_00]: But there were no trees, hedgerows or anything like that that you could use for cover.

11:35.627 --> 11:36.589
[SPEAKER_01]: Right.

