[SPEAKER_01]: Ed, I know that you and your wife, Jeannie, were married for 61 years.

26:08.968 --> 26:14.973
[SPEAKER_01]: You lost her just earlier this year, but obviously she was someone who supported you.

26:15.033 --> 26:19.277
[SPEAKER_01]: You all were married when you had gone off to war, is that right?

26:19.297 --> 26:21.479
[SPEAKER_00]: Well, no, we got married in 1944.

26:21.739 --> 26:30.047
[SPEAKER_00]: I had been overseas at one time and back, and then we got together again and got married and have been married.

26:30.247 --> 26:32.949
[SPEAKER_01]: And there were a lot of letters that went back and forth.

26:33.069 --> 26:34.030
[SPEAKER_00]: Oh, yeah, you bet.

26:34.010 --> 26:36.153
[SPEAKER_01]: Absolutely.

26:36.173 --> 26:42.080
[SPEAKER_01]: And I know that she was a very big supporter of yours and very much a part of your life, 61 years.

26:42.121 --> 26:45.124
[SPEAKER_00]: That's absolutely... She was a very special lady.

26:45.144 --> 26:45.986
[SPEAKER_01]: Very special lady.

